The paper focuses on the security architecture and protocols of 5G networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The evaluation of the 5G security specifications also involves analyzing the system requirements and processes, which could be classified under software engineering (cs.SE) and systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses potential vulnerabilities and exploits, which could be relevant to cyber-physical systems (cs.CY).
